; ─── PHASE 2: DIVERGENCE REPORT ──────────────────────────────────────

(divergence-report
  :axis-1-r7rs-compliance
  ("Neither Motoi nor Sakura had `define-record-type` — GAP, both-wrong."
   "Neither Motoi nor Sakura had exception system (`guard`/`raise`/`error-object?`) — GAP."
   "Neither had `do` iteration form — GAP."
   "Neither had `delay`/`force` (lazy evaluation) — GAP."
   "Neither had hash tables — GAP (Sakura substrate had corpus-attested `hash-ref`, resolved by adding both the SRFI-125 surface and the alias)."
   "Neither had bytevectors — GAP."
   "Neither had string ports — GAP."
   "Both had `ceiling` and `ceil` — R7RS spelling is `ceiling`, `ceil` is an alias for the beginner-friendlier short-form (already documented in existing meta).")

  :axis-2-sakura-vs-motoi
  ("Base library (arithmetic, list ops, string ops, higher-order, equality): IDENTICAL between Motoi and Sakura src/base.js — verified line-by-line."
   "Special-forms: IDENTICAL before this pass; also IDENTICAL after (both got same additions)."
   "Reader: IDENTICAL parse rules."
   "Macro expander: IDENTICAL (both have `define-syntax`+`syntax-rules` subset)."
   "Divergence found: Sakura's base.js additionally wires LLM/persona/completions (correctly — Sakura is business-side, CAN reach internet). This is EXPECTED per Sakura-CAN-contact-internet doctrine."
   "Motoi's base.js does NOT wire LLM/persona/completions — CORRECT per Motoi-no-tools-no-internet doctrine.")

  :axis-3-motoi-sakura-inheritance
  ("With the FILL PASS applied to BOTH dialects, inheritance is now complete on the R7RS surface."
   "Every R7RS-small verb behaves identically. Every SRFI-1/13/125 verb behaves identically."
   "Sakura's Section 7B (Priya audit) hash-ref promoted to CORE alias for hash-table-ref, matching Motoi."
   "No inheritance-breaking divergences found.")

  :fix-count 0
  :note "The FILL PASS took care of the gaps; no post-hoc FIX PASS needed. Motoi and Sakura had identical bugs (all missing R7RS surface); adding the R7RS surface to both is the fix.")

