    "fold — SRFI-1 left fold (had reduce but not fold; standard SRFI-1 spelling)"
    "make-hash-table / hash-table-set! / hash-table-ref / hash-ref — SRFI-125 hash tables (both dialects had ZERO hash-table surface pre-pass)"
    "define-record-type — R7RS §5.5 record types (structural typing for domain values)"
    "guard / error / raise / error-object? — R7RS §6.11 exception system (previously no way to catch errors in-Scheme)"))

; ─── PHASE 4: FIX PASS ───────────────────────────────────────────────

(fix-pass
  :count 0
  :note "No functional divergences between Motoi and Sakura were found beyond the shared R7RS gaps addressed by the FILL PASS. Both interpreters had identical special-form coverage pre-pass; identical arithmetic/list/string surface; identical error shapes. The FILL PASS closes gaps in both simultaneously.")

; ─── PHASE 5: MODULES-vs-CORE DECISION ───────────────────────────────

(modules-vs-core-decision
  :core-motoi (
    :description "Every verb loaded by every Motoi runtime, no import needed."
    :count-approx 455
    :includes (
      "R7RS-small (base library, special forms) — 100%"
      "SRFI-1 list conveniences — the daily set (fold/iota/find/partition/filter-map/append-map/positional accessors)"
      "SRFI-13 string conveniences — the daily set (split/join/trim/pad/upcase/downcase)"
      "SRFI-125 hash tables (canonical R7RS-large-track set)"
      "R7RS §6.9 bytevectors"
      "R7RS §6.10 string ports (file ports intentionally omitted — hermetic Motoi)"
      "R7RS §6.11 exceptions"
      "R7RS §5.5 records"
      "R7RS §4.2.4/§4.2.5 do / delay / force"
      "Motoi-specific game/fantasy-console library (already core: framebuffer/sprite/audio/entity/ai/etc.)"
      "SLAT primitives"
      "Artifact primitives (headless stubs; browser-side reals)"))

  :core-sakura (
    :description "Identical CORE tier to Motoi, plus Sakura's dialect-neutral base."
    :count-approx 455
    :inheritance "Same R7RS surface as Motoi core."
    :additional-in-sakura-base "LLM tier-0 (llm/*), sakura/* persona wrappers, completions/*")

  :module-motoi (
    :description "Loaded via (import (module-name)). None declared at finalization — Motoi ships with everything in core."
    :count 0
    :note "Motoi is intentionally a small, focused base. Future module candidates (SRFI-64 test suite, SRFI-14 char sets, network I/O) are not added.")

  :module-sakura (
    :description "Dialect verbs loaded by installers per dialect surface."
    :count-approx 102
    :includes (
      "card/* — big-0.85 Wave 2, src/lib/dialect/card/"
      "shop/* — big-0.85 Wave 2, src/lib/dialect/shop/"
      "flower/* — big-0.85 Wave 2, src/lib/dialect/flower/"
      "cortex/* — big-0.85 Wave 2, src/lib/dialect/cortex/"
      "surface/* — Section 1"
      "artifact/* — Section 6"
      "speech/* — Priya audit Section 7B"
      "system/* + time/* — Priya audit Section 7B"
      "audio family (adsr/wave/noise) — Priya audit Section 7B (needs-alfred-verification)"))

  :justification (
    "R7RS-small is the baseline every Scheme is expected to have. Making it CORE means beginner Scheme code Just Works. If we module-gated R7RS itself, every cart would start with (import (r7rs)) — needless boilerplate."
    "SRFI-1/13/125 daily-use verbs are what a working Scheme author reaches for constantly (fold, iota, find, string-split, hash-table-ref). Module-gating them would mean every non-trivial cart repeats the import boilerplate."
    "Specialty SRFI verbs (unfold, string-fold, complex hash-table constructors with equality-predicates + hash-fn) are NOT added — those are candidates for future module surfaces if demand emerges."
    "Sakura dialect verbs (card/*, shop/*, etc.) stay MODULE because they're domain-specific. A Sakura cart that doesn't touch cards shouldn't pay for card/* symbol pollution."))

; ─── PHASE 6: CONSISTENCY + BEAUTY PASS ──────────────────────────────

(beauty-pass
  :reference-shape-audit (
    :consistent "Every added verb has :name, :library, :tier, :kind, :signature, :summary, :provenance."
    :examples-added-count 63
    :two-plus-examples "Novice + intermediate examples for the 20 most-used verbs (iota, fold, string-split, hash-table-set!, define-record-type, guard, do, error, etc.)"
    :one-line-doc "Short verbs (second..tenth, char predicates, comparison alias verbs) get single-line summaries — R7RS-shaped brevity."
    :error-shape "Every error follows (error msg irritants...) — R7RS §6.11 canonical. Verified by test suite."
    :cross-refs "Every :related list references verbs that exist."
    :provenance-citation "Every add cites R7RS section or SRFI number.")

  :docstring-voice (
    "Written for humans, not machines. Short prose. No jargon. Example first when useful."
    "Verbs come first (\"Read one line from port.\") not \"This function reads...\""
    "Consistent use of R7RS §X.Y citations at end of :summary."
    "Beginner-friendly examples paired with intermediate examples when the shape is non-obvious.")

  :graph-node-shape (
    "R7RS completions do not need graph-of-* nodes at finalization — they're standard verbs with standard behavior, not doctrine-carrying nodes."
    "Sakura-specific dialect verbs (Sections 1-8) retain their graph structure."))

